Well, according to Secretary of State Tillerson,

147
00:05:45,580 --> 00:05:46,749
Trump brought it up…

148
00:05:46,749 --> 00:05:48,349
but didn't really say anything

149
00:05:48,349 --> 00:05:50,440
that Xi Jinping can't just ignore.

150
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:54,120
So actually, that’s a point for Xi.

151
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,629
What about human rights—

152
00:05:55,629 --> 00:05:57,360
something that Trump was urged to bring up

153
00:05:57,360 --> 00:05:58,740
during the meeting?

154
00:05:58,740 --> 00:05:59,900
Tillerson said that Trump

155
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:02,840
"also noted the importance of protecting human
rights

156
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:06,050
and other values deeply held by Americans."

157
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:08,440
Well, that's good.

158
00:06:08,449 --> 00:06:10,080
But when a reporter asked Tillerson

159
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:12,279
whether the Trump Administration would pressure
China

160
00:06:12,279 --> 00:06:15,259
on specific human rights violations,

161
00:06:15,259 --> 00:06:16,259
here's what he said:

162
00:06:16,259 --> 00:06:20,740
As to the discussions around human rights in China,

163
00:06:20,740 --> 00:06:23,460
I think America’s values are quite clear

164
00:06:23,460 --> 00:06:27,260
and they really occupied a core of all of
our discussions.

165
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:30,939
I don't think you have to have a separate
conversation...

166
00:06:30,939 --> 00:06:34,789
They’re really embedded in every discussion.

167
00:06:34,789 --> 00:06:38,129
So human rights are part of being American

168
00:06:38,129 --> 00:06:41,789
so we don't have to talk separately about
human rights

169
00:06:41,789 --> 00:06:43,850
because we're American?

170
00:06:43,850 --> 00:06:46,119
I'm going to interpret that as no,

171
00:06:46,119 --> 00:06:47,369
we did not talk to China

172
00:06:47,369 --> 00:06:49,520
about their human rights violations.

173
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:51,100
I'm disappointed in you, T-Rex.

174
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:53,860
Another point for Xi.

175
00:06:53,879 --> 00:06:57,399
And the two are tied again.

176
00:06:57,399 --> 00:07:00,550
Now comes the contentious North Korea issue.

177
00:07:00,550 --> 00:07:02,559
Ninety percent of the rogue regime’s trade

178
00:07:02,559 --> 00:07:04,569
is done with China.

179
00:07:04,569 --> 00:07:06,189
But getting the Chinese Communist Party

180
00:07:06,189 --> 00:07:08,050
to turn on its little brother

181
00:07:08,050 --> 00:07:10,020
has been difficult.

182
00:07:10,020 --> 00:07:11,039
But at Mar-a-Lago,

183
00:07:11,039 --> 00:07:12,120
Xi Jinping agreed that

184
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:16,659
“action had to be taken” against North
Korea.

185
00:07:16,659 --> 00:07:18,729
Probably launching that missile strike on
Syria

186
00:07:18,729 --> 00:07:21,439
helped Trump get his point across, too.

187
00:07:21,439 --> 00:07:24,370
Now it looks like China is taking some action.

188
00:07:24,370 --> 00:07:26,389
They just sent back North Korea coal ships

189
00:07:26,389 --> 00:07:29,189
as part of UN sanctions.

190
00:07:29,189 --> 00:07:31,389
And they're also talking again to South Korea

191
00:07:31,389 --> 00:07:35,039
about hitting North Korea with more sanctions.

192
00:07:35,039 --> 00:07:37,850
That is a solid point for Trump.

193
00:07:37,850 --> 00:07:40,149
But it’s also a win for Xi Jinping,

194
00:07:40,149 --> 00:07:41,569
because giving the appearance

195
00:07:41,569 --> 00:07:43,499
