196
00:07:43,499 --> 00:07:46,280
prevents the US from acting on its own,

197
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:49,110
which would have put China in a very awkward
spot.

198
00:07:49,110 --> 00:07:52,279
Plus Xi Jinping already wanted to contain
North Korea,

199
00:07:52,279 --> 00:07:54,610
so this is a good excuse for him.

200
00:07:54,610 --> 00:07:57,750
I’d say it’s more of a win than a concession.

201
00:07:57,750 --> 00:08:01,349
So Xi deserves a point for that, too.

202
00:08:01,349 --> 00:08:03,280
Now, how about trade?

203
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:06,249
Surely, someone will break this tie.

204
00:08:06,249 --> 00:08:09,300
China has enjoyed a huge trade surplus with
the US

205
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:11,539
for more than two decades.

206
00:08:11,539 --> 00:08:15,729
Last year, it stood at 347 billion dollars.

207
00:08:15,729 --> 00:08:18,180
And all those exports have been propping up

208
00:08:18,180 --> 00:08:19,830
China’s economy.

209
00:08:19,830 --> 00:08:21,150
So Trump comes into the ring

210
00:08:21,150 --> 00:08:24,259
with harsh rhetoric about these trade imbalances.

211
00:08:24,259 --> 00:08:25,550
At the meeting,

212
00:08:25,550 --> 00:08:27,080
according to Financial Times,

213
00:08:27,080 --> 00:08:29,669
Xi Jinping “offered the Trump administration

214
00:08:29,669 --> 00:08:33,620
better market access for financial sector
investments.”

215
